fields.text: CR to be raised for restart
Get access to box from security
The log file has been uploaded to sharepoint and the clean room common folder. A print out was also posted to the clean room.
Closed because the Managed Servers are now displaying the correct status after increasing the message sizes of the incoming messages to 15 million.
Log File Inventory completed and uploaded on the sharepoint. A printout has been placed in the clean room for the location of the log files
The job has been scheduled to start on the 5/08/2015 and will run every 15 minutes. I will check the performance of this tomorrow.

The thresholds wereset to;
Warning: 80
Critical: 95.

This is why we were not alerted.
We have chosen to leave these alerts the way they are currently configured.
The incident report has been sent to the SM team.
The script seems to be running correctly. The next step will be to add the metric extension so that we can generate alerts.
Juliani is going to provide assistance
Generic Services have been renamed from OEG and HTB to OAG and HDR respectively.
All items have been added to share point.
Alerts have been confirmed in both SDC and PDC.
There was two sets of rules that were essentially doing the same thing.
Reports and metrix extensions have been cleaned. However as I do not know the purpose of all of them I simply just deleted duplicates and ones that were clearly old and unused.
I am going to work with Jyoti to integrate a patch report with her start stop scripts.
The metric extensions and incident rules were implemented however there are issues in the collection/alerts

The alerts are in place and working as expected.
Metric Extension: Log_Parser_Monitor
Incident Rule: SMS Notification -> OAAM LOG PARSER MONITOR
